OL,3,CFather of two who has had four liver
OL,4,Ctransplants 'forever grateful' to
OL,5,Cdonors
OL,7,FThe transplant was a success, and the
OL,8,F29-year-old welder was able to enjoy a
OL,9,Fnormal childhood and adolescence with
OL,10,Fhis twin brother Stuart.
OL,12,FHowever in September 2022 Mr Dillett
OL,13,Fbegan experiencing health issues, and
OL,14,Fa few months later he learned that the
OL,15,Fliver that had kept him alive for the
OL,16,Fpast 25 years was beginning to fail.
OL,18,F"My liver wasn't functioning properly,
OL,19,Fso it was putting a lot more pressure
OL,20,Fon my kidneys and all my other organs
OL,21,Fto help out," he said.
OL,26,@zD@AOU}D@MO]
