OL,3,CFather of two who has had four liver
OL,4,Ctransplants 'forever grateful' to
OL,5,Cdonors
OL,7,F"We were told Martin was severely
OL,8,Funwell and he may not survive the
OL,9,Fsurgery."
OL,11,FThe liver was completely removed,
OL,12,Fmaking Mr Dillett only the third
OL,13,Fpatient in the unit's 30-year history
OL,14,Fto be without a liver while awaiting a
OL,15,Ftransplant.
OL,17,FMrs Dillett recalled: "We were nearly
OL,18,Fout of hope. The doctors said if
OL,19,FMartin didn't get another liver in the
OL,20,Fnext 12 to 24 hours he wouldn't
OL,21,Fsurvive.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@IO]yD@WOU
