OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F303A1727139427
OL,3,CFather of two who has had four liver
OL,4,Ctransplants 'forever grateful' to
OL,5,Cdonors
OL,7,F"We were told to expect the worst. We
OL,8,Fgot told to bring in family to
OL,9,Fbasically say our goodbyes. I really
OL,10,Fthought we were going to lose him.
OL,11,FEvery half-hour counted."
OL,13,FMr Dillett spent a total of 36 hours
OL,14,Fwithout a liver before a suitable one
OL,15,Fwas found, and successfully
OL,16,Ftransplanted into his body.
OL,18,FThe 29-year-old said he was "lucky" to
OL,19,Fhave survived, and that he was "hugely
OL,20,Fthankful" to the staff at the RIE for
OL,21,Fnot giving up on him.
